e mute evasion (Mute : prevents you to speak on the in Games chat box) and Ban evasion (Ban : prevents you to access to the Games). Evading a mute or ban will result in a higher punishment.. If you feel that you were punished unfairly, you can contact the moderation directly or use the <a href="<?=$site?>/contact" target="_blank" rel="noopener" onclick="return verifierLienMemePageMessage(event);">contact form</a> .<br /><span style="font-weight:bold;">(e)</span>When a player bothers you in game, you can propose a vote to the other players present in order to ban them from your room with the command /ban called voteban. Voteban abuse is prohibited. Abuse means getting together with friends or tribe members to purposely ban any random player for no reason. It’s prohibited to use the voteban indiscriminately or for fun. This command is dedicated exclusively to ban players disturbing the room.<br /><span style="font-weight:bold;">(f)</span> Tribe names violating these Terms and/or the Rules of Conduct.<br /><span style="font-weight:bold;">(g)</span> Leaking/Sharing private information relevant to the Games, leaking/sharing private information on another player, harassing another player on the Games or third-party software used to communicate with players of the Games.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight:bold;">Information on Phishing and Scams:</span><br />Any method of obtaining in-game items or credits (“Fraise”, “Cheese”, “Hazelnut”, “Potato”) outside of the Games is illegal. These illegal sources often require players to provide their username, password and e-mails, and create a huge security risk. These websites are often an imitation of the real website and are controlled by a malicious person. If the user enters any personal information, they will be transmitted directly to the scammer .Upon discovery of any player promoting or using these illegal websites, we will take serious action. <?=$ayarlar['title']?> and The Games are in no way affiliated with these website and don’t support them. Please report any players advertising or using a phishing website. You can report them directly to the moderation or via the <a href="<?=$site?>/ " target="_blank" rel="noopener" onclick="return verifierLienMemePageMessage(event);">contact form</a>.
